      "min": 25,
      "max": 75,
      "step": 5,
      "default": 45
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "heading_size_min",
      "label": "Heading Min Size — Mobile floor (px)",
      "min": 18,
      "max": 40,
      "step": 1,
      "default": 28
    },

    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "── Body Paragraphs ──"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "paragraph_1",
      "label": "Paragraph 1",
      "default": "<p>We didn't need to import a framework for sex. Intimacy wasn't always reduced to technique or outcome. There was a time when it was understood as something deeper, something to be explored, not rushed.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "richtext",
      "id": "paragraph_2",
      "label": "Paragraph 2",
      "default": "<p>Our own tradition, which saw sex as science, poetry, and self-knowledge, was quietly buried. The Kamasutra was not lost. It was colonised out of our consciousness.</p>"
